76561197972025376,Recommended,328590,34766142,Posted: 5 September,all,justintd,"It took me 100 minutes to beat this. It's very similar to Paranormal Activity, except PA takes about twice as long to finish. DKT has nice graphics and sound. There are multiple jump scares, and I yelled out loud 3 or 4 times. There are teleport and free locomotion options. I used the free locomotion option, and it was a little hard to control, and you'd sometimes get stuck on objects. The doors are a little hard to open sometimes too. For $15, I recommend it but not for $20 due to the length.Edit: I forgot to mention that achievements pop up often and are annoying, so I turned off notifications in Steam VR settings when playing this game. Problem solved."
76561198019046685,Recommended,328590,35004127,Posted: 16 September,all,Hooded Crow,"I do feel this game is well worth the buy and offers great atmosphere as well as gameplay however I do think it's lacking in the scare department.  Comparing this to ""Paranormal Activity""  I'd say the graphical quality is just as good and even feels  a little more alive in some ways.  Price point is a no brainer, especially since the overall length of the story is maybe slightly shorter the PA but pretty close to the same.  PA does offer actual danger however where this game is just you progressing forward with maybe two or three scripted scares. I can understand not wanting to rely on jump scares to heavily but overall I didn't get much of a thrill out of this game and wish there was at least some way to lose the game.  I'd say definitely buy it as a surreal story driven game that offers a beautifully crafted house to explore with attention to detail in every crevice but don't expect to wet your pants."
