,Not Recommended,328590,35096738,Posted: 20 September,all,MatiasBaci,"TL;DRDon't buy this game, getA Chair In A Roominstead.PROS+Some very nice scares. Good tension.+Some good use of the VR medium, like swinging the axe to break open doors and lighting candles.+For a short horror game, the story is good. There's not much of it, just enough if you're interested in it. I liked the ending as well.CONS-Buggy controls. The trigger kept being spammed, making it extremely difficult to navigate the main menu, and annoying to read papers or use flamethrower. Plus the player moves too slowly.-Buggy physics. Very weird hitboxes and collisions. I often got stuck just by walking close to things. Waving objects such as the axe feels very awkward, and they often get stuck on walls and objects. Unlocked doors sometimes get stuck.-Bad graphics. Reflections look like there is a smaller, wallpainted version of the room on the other side.-Some things look like they should be much smaller in the real world. Glass that is like 5cm thick, just things that make the game more unimmersive.-Achievement progress kept ruining immersion too. A lot of notifications pop up during the game.To the devsA few suggestions that might help:1) Allow for both forms of locomotion at the same time. Could help when the player gets stuck using trackpad locomotion.2) Custom trackpad movement speed.3) Add the ability to store essential items like map and axe on the waist, just like the cellphone."
